        "description": "MetaStoreDirectSql constructor is querying DB to determine dbType, which leads to too many DB queries to make megastore slow as ObjectStore.setConf might be called frequently. Moreover, ObjectStore.setConf begins/ends with lock acquire/release, if the underlying DB hangs somehow, lock is never released and all hereafter incoming requests are blocked.\n\nTwo points:\n1. Using getProductName based JDBC driver to get dbType info.\n2. Since metastore auto-creaton is disabled by default, it'd better bypass ensureDbInit() and runTestQuery() in order to avoid DB queries within critical section of setConf.\n\nHere\u2019s stack trace:\nMetaStoreDirectSql.determineDbType(...)\nMetaStoreDirectSql.MetaStoreDirectSql(...)\nObjectStore.initialize(...)\nObjectStore.setConf(\u2026)\n\n",
